My current holdings and their values are

- Wheat 13 × 6 = 78  
- Wood  15 × 9 = 135  
- Sheep 14 × 18 = 252  
- Brick  9 × 23 = 207  
- Ore   23 × 38 = 874  
Total value = 1 546

Key facts so far  
- Player 1 is very reluctant to give up Brick or Ore; every time I’ve targeted those, they’ve balked.  
- They have attempted to *get* Brick from me twice, paying in Wood/Sheep/Ore. I refused because my valuation of Brick (23) meant the trades were not profitable.  

I need moves that actually profit me while respecting their aversion to losing Brick/Ore. My cheapest resources are Wheat/Wood, highest value is Ore. I am happy to reduce weaker cards if I gain value elsewhere.  

Looking at my totals, I still have 15 Wood and 13 Wheat – very plentiful – so those remain the easiest currencies. I can give up 3-4 Wood/Wheat without hurting my hand.

Proposal  
I will try a **low-impact but high-value-for-them** ask: a single extra Brick for three of my weakest cards. It moves little value out of my position but uses their surplus resources (they keep turning down huge asks, so fewer asks are worth testing).

[Offer: 3 Wheat, 2 Wood -> 1 Brick, 1 Wheat]
